We need to pick out depreciation‐related transactions and see what they contribute. In these transactions the “Depreciation” record is the only one that affects accumulated depreciation. (No previous depreciation has been recorded on the balance sheet.) In our list we see the following depreciation record:

• ID Depreciation20240101001 – Type: Depreciation – Date: 2024‑01‑01 – Amount: 45,757.71

Since there is no prior accumulated depreciation (the Fixed Assets were recorded as an initial value, but no depreciation has been posted before this event), the accumulated depreciation initial value is zero. Then, after posting the depreciation expense for the period the total accumulated depreciation becomes 45,757.71.

Thus the answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Accumulated Depreciation Initial Value": "0.00",
    "Accumulated Depreciation End Value": "45757.71"
  }
